<TITLE> Govt to supply textbooks by Dec </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, Dec 11 (bdnews24.com)  The education ministry will distribute textbooks among the students by December, said education minister Nurul Islam Nahid Friday. The present government wants to bring about a 'revolutionary change' in education, transportation and agricultural sectors, Nahid said at an inaugural ceremony of development plan of Saudakhal bridge in Bianibazar. While addressing the opening ceremony of the new building of Khasha Government Primary School he said, "I am being threatened to stop formulating a new education policy. But I will not." Among the others, Bianibazar upazila parishad chairman Abdul Khaliq Mayan and Awami Leader Haji Abdul Hasib Mania addressed the meetings. bdnew
